//! glow/lower_bartis.rye — lower a thin `|=` bartis gate to runnable `.rye` (STOA100–107).
//!
//! Identity gate: `|=  sample=@u32` / `sample` — takes u32 and returns it.
//! Call body: `|=  sample=@u32` / `%-  <gate>  sample` — closed demos:
//!   double → *% 2 (STOA103) · inc → +% 1 · dec → -% 1 (STOA104).
//! STOA100: baked demo sample 5; identity exits 0 when bartis_gate(5) == 5.
//! STOA101: argv sample path — main reads one decimal `@u32` and checks the body result.
//! STOA105: TAME tidy — assert · u32 · append_print · split emitters.
//! STOA107: nest/type surface — non-`@u32` sample refuses `SampleDoesNotNest`.
//! STOA109 / STOA122: named molds `amount-mold` · `count-mold` lower as `@u32`.
//! STOA123: `kind-mold` identity lowers as `KindShape` enum · baked `.mint`.
//! STOA124: `xact-mold` identity lowers as `XactShape` union · baked `.mint` amount 5.
//! STOA125: `xfer-mold` identity lowers as `XferShape` union · baked `.mint` from 5 amount 3.
//! STOA126: `pair-mold` identity lowers as `PairShape` struct · baked from 5 amount 3.
//! STOA134: `triple-mold` identity lowers as `TripleShape` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1.
//! STOA135: `quad-mold` identity lowers as `QuadShape` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1 nonce 2.
//! STOA136: `triple-mold` call body `%-  flip` → TripleShape swap · baked 5/3/1 → 3/5/1.
//! STOA137: `quad-mold` call body `%-  flip` → QuadShape swap · baked 5/3/1/2 → 3/5/1/2.
//! STOA138: `penta-mold` identity lowers as `PentaShape` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1 nonce 2 memo 7.
//! STOA139: `penta-mold` call body `%-  flip` → PentaShape swap · baked 5/3/1/2/7 → 3/5/1/2/7.
//! STOA140: `hexa-mold` identity lowers as `HexaShape` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1 nonce 2 memo 7 tag 4.
//! STOA141: `hexa-mold` call body `%-  flip` → HexaShape swap · baked 5/3/1/2/7/4 → 3/5/1/2/7/4.
//! STOA142: `hepta-mold` identity lowers as `HeptaShape` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1 nonce 2 memo 7 tag 4 to 6.
//! STOA143: `hepta-mold` call body `%-  flip` → HeptaShape swap · baked 5/3/1/2/7/4/6 → 3/5/1/2/7/4/6.
//! STOA144: `octa-mold` identity lowers as `OctaShape` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1 nonce 2 memo 7 tag 4 to 6 via 8.
//! STOA145: `octa-mold` call body `%-  flip` → OctaShape swap · baked 5/3/1/2/7/4/6/8 → 3/5/1/2/7/4/6/8.
//! STOA146: `nona-mold` identity lowers as `NonaShape` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1 nonce 2 memo 7 tag 4 to 6 via 8 ref 9.
//! STOA147: `nona-mold` call body `%-  flip` → NonaShape swap · baked 5/3/1/2/7/4/6/8/9 → 3/5/1/2/7/4/6/8/9.
//! STOA253: pair…nona identity emit collapses through `emit_n_field_identity`
//! (faces · demos shared).
//! STOA259: pair…nona flip call-body collapses through `emit_n_field_flip_call_body`
//! (same faces · demos; from↔amount swap).
//! STOA127: `kind-mold` call body `%-  flip` → KindShape switch · baked `.mint` → `.send`.
//! STOA128: `xact-mold` call body `%-  flip` → XactShape switch · baked mint/5 → `.send`.
//! STOA129: `xfer-mold` call body `%-  flip` → XferShape switch · baked mint/5/3 → `.send`.
//! STOA293: xact+xfer flip call-body collapses through `emit_tagged_payload_flip_call_body`
//!   (mint_faces 1|2). Kind unit flip stays its own family.
//! STOA297: kind flip call-body collapses through `emit_tagged_unit_flip_call_body`.
//! STOA131: `pair-mold` call body `%-  flip` → PairShape swap · baked 5/3 → 3/5.
//! STOA132: `amount-mold` argv identity — generator beside fixture (u32-shaped named mold).
//! STOA133: `count-mold` argv identity — twin generator beside fixture.
//! STOA300: `kind-mold` argv identity — unit-tag reader (`mint`/`send`).
//! STOA303: `xact-mold` argv identity — payload tag + amount (`mint <u32>` / `send`).
//! STOA305: `xfer-mold` argv identity — payload tag + two mint faces (`mint <from> <amount>` / `send`).
//! STOA307: `pair-mold` argv identity — `$:` two-field reader (`<from> <amount>`).
//! STOA309: `triple-mold` argv identity — `$:` three-field reader (`<from> <amount> <fee>`).
//! STOA311: `quad-mold` argv identity — `$:` four-field reader (`<from> <amount> <fee> <nonce>`).
//! STOA313: `penta-mold` argv identity — `$:` five-field reader (`… <memo>`); hexa…nona held.
//! Gate function named `bartis_gate` to avoid collisions with the sample face.

const std = @import("std");
const assert = std.debug.assert;
const rb = @import("rune_bartis.rye");
const nest_type = @import("nest_type.rye");

pub const LowerError = rb.ParseError || error{Overflow};

